\begin_layout Subsection
Relaciones entre módulos.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{defi}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

{
\end_layout

\end_inset

Módulo o valor absoluto
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

{
\end_layout

\end_inset

dmod
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
El módulo o valor absoluto de un número real, 
\begin_inset Formula $a,$
\end_inset

 se representa por 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|a\right|$
\end_inset

 (se lee módulo de 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

) y se define 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left|a\right|=\left\{ \begin{array}{ccc}
-a & \text{si} & a<0\\
0 & \text{si} & a=0\\
a & \text{si} & a>0
\end{array}\right.\label{eq:modulo}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defi}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{ejemplos}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|-3\right|=-\left(-3\right)=3$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|0\right|=0.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|3\right|=3.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{ejemplos}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
De acuerdo con las reglas del cálculo con números reales, recordamos que
 se cumplen las siguientes relaciones:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{propiedad}{
\backslash
hspace{-2pt}:
\backslash
 Propiedad triangular}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
El módulo de una suma de números reales es igual o menor que la suma de
 los módulos de los sumandos.
 resulta igual a la suma de los módulos cuando todos los sumandos son del
 mismo signo.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{propiedad}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{ejemplos}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|5-2+3-4+1\right|<\left|5\right|+\left|-2\right|+\left|3\right|+\left|-4\right|+\left|1\right|$
\end_inset

 entonces 
\begin_inset Formula $3<15.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|-2-5-7\right|=\left|-2\right|+\left|-5\right|+\left|-7\right|$
\end_inset

 entonces 
\begin_inset Formula $-\left(-14\right)=\left|-14\right|=2+5+7=14.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|3+6\right|=\left|3\right|+\left|6\right|=9.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{ejemplos}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{propiedad}{}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
El módulo de un producto es igual al producto de los módulos.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{propiedad}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Es decir 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|a\cdot b\right|=\left|a\right|\cdot\left|b\right|.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{ejemplos}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|-3\cdot2\right|=\left|-3\right|\cdot\left|2\right|=6.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\left(-2\right)\cdot\left(-5\right)\right|=\left|-2\right|\cdot\left|-5\right|=2\cdot5=10.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{ejemplos}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{propiedad}{}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
El módulo de un cociente es igual al cociente de los módulos.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{propiedad}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Es decir, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\dfrac{a}{b}\right|=\dfrac{\left|a\right|}{\left|b\right|},\;b\neq0.$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{ejemplos}
